<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="114" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="1" pageNumber="114">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="1" pageNumber="114">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tagane &amp; V. S. Dang" authorityYear="2017" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Loranthaceae" genus="Macrosolen" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Macrosolen bidoupensis" order="Santalales" pageId="1" pageNumber="114" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bidoupensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="114">Macrosolen bidoupensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Danser" authorityYear="1929" baseAuthorityName="Lecomte" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Loranthaceae" genus="Macrosolen" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Macrosolen tricolor" order="Santalales" pageId="1" pageNumber="114" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tricolor">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="114">Macrosolen tricolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Danser of China, Laos and Vietnam in leaf shape and size and by possession of a 2-flowered umbel, but differs in having a sessile to very short petiole (up to 0.7 mm long in 
<taxonomicName class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Loranthaceae" genus="M." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="M. bidoupensis" order="Santalales" pageId="1" pageNumber="114" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="bidoupensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="114">M. bidoupensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
vs. 2-3 mm long in 
<taxonomicName class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Loranthaceae" genus="M." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="M. tricolor" order="Santalales" pageId="1" pageNumber="114" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="tricolor">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="114">M. tricolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), more lateral veins (4 or 5 vs. 2 or 3 pairs), slightly cordate to rounded leaf bases (vs. cuneate) and a basally green corolla tube (vs. reddish around the basal 1/3). The leaf shape is also somewhat similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Danser" authorityYear="1929" baseAuthorityName="King" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Loranthaceae" genus="Macrosolen" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Macrosolen platyphyllus" order="Santalales" pageId="1" pageNumber="114" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="platyphyllus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="114">Macrosolen platyphyllus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Danser of Thailand, Peninsular Malaysia and Borneo, but easily distinguished in having much smaller leaves and flowers, and very short petioles.
</paragraph>
